<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n53123s"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n53" href="#n53123s">N53 (VI.B.46)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n53all.htm#n53123s"> 123(s)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Rudraka,</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Le h&eacute;ros apprit que, pr&egrave;s de R&acirc;jagriha, vivait un asc&egrave;te illustre, <mark>Roudraka</mark>, fils de R&acirc;ma, qui enseignait la loi &agrave; de nombreux disciples. Il alla &eacute;couter ses le&ccedil;ons; mais, non plus qu&apos;Ar&acirc;ta-K&acirc;l&acirc;ma, Roudraka ne connaissait la vraie loi, et le h&eacute;ros ne s&apos;attarda pas aupr&egrave;s de lui. <small> A. Ferdinand Herold, <a name="AFHB" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#AFHB"><cite title="source">La Vie Du Bouddha</cite></a> (1922) 72</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Siddharta went to Roudaka and listened to his philosophy, but was unimpressed. </mm> </dd></dl>
